msgctxt "an8.57:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 8 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 8 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:0.2"
msgid "6. Gotamīvagga "
msgstr "6. Gotamī "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
#. VAR: 57. Paṭhamaāhuneyyasutta → paṭhamaāhuneyyabhikkhusuttaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "an8.57:0.3"
msgid "57. Paṭhamaāhuneyyasutta "
msgstr "57. Worthy of Offerings to the Gods (1st) "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli4.291, sc1
msgctxt "an8.57:1.1"
msgid "“Aṭṭhahi, bhikkhave, dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti pāhuneyyo dakkhiṇeyyo añjalikaraṇīyo anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassa. "
msgstr "“Mendicants, a mendicant with eight factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world. "

msgctxt "an8.57:1.2"
msgid "Katamehi aṭṭhahi? "
msgstr "What eight? "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.3"
msgid "Idha, bhikkhave, bhikkhu sīlavā hoti … pe … samādāya sikkhati sikkhāpadesu; "
msgstr "It’s when a mendicant is ethical, restrained in the code of conduct, with good behavior and supporters. Seeing danger in the slightest fault, they keep the rules they’ve undertaken. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.4"
msgid "bahussuto hoti … pe … diṭṭhiyā suppaṭividdhā; "
msgstr "They’re learned, remembering and keeping what they’ve learned. These teachings are good in the beginning, good in the middle, and good in the end, meaningful and well-phrased, describing a spiritual practice that’s totally full and pure. They are very learned in such teachings, remembering them, reciting them, mentally scrutinizing them, and understanding them with right view. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.5"
msgid "kalyāṇamitto hoti kalyāṇasahāyo kalyāṇasampavaṅko; "
msgstr "They have good friends, companions, and associates. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.6"
msgid "sammādiṭṭhiko hoti, sammādassanena samannāgato; "
msgstr "They have right view, possessing right perspective. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.7"
msgid "catunnaṃ jhānānaṃ ābhicetasikānaṃ diṭṭhadhammasukhavihārānaṃ nikāmalābhī hoti akicchalābhī akasiralābhī; "
msgstr "They get the four absorptions—blissful meditations in the present life that belong to the higher mind—when they want, without trouble or difficulty. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.8"
msgid "anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati, seyyathidaṃ—ekampi jātiṃ dvepi jātiyo … pe … iti sākāraṃ sauddesaṃ anekavihitaṃ pubbenivāsaṃ anussarati; "
msgstr "They recollect many kinds of past lives, with features and details. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.9"
msgid "dibbena cakkhunā visuddhena atikkantamānusakena … pe … yathākammūpage satte pajānāti; "
msgstr "With clairvoyance that is purified and surpasses the human, they see how sentient beings are reborn according to their deeds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.10"
msgid "āsavānaṃ khayā … pe … sacchikatvā upasampajja viharati. "
msgstr "They realize the undefiled freedom of heart and freedom by wisdom in this very life. And they live having realized it with their own insight due to the ending of defilements. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an8.57:1.11"
msgid "Imehi kho, bhikkhave, aṭṭhahi dhammehi samannāgato bhikkhu āhuneyyo hoti … pe … anuttaraṃ puññakkhettaṃ lokassā”ti. "
msgstr "A mendicant with these eight factors is worthy of offerings dedicated to the gods, worthy of hospitality, worthy of a religious donation, worthy of veneration with joined palms, and is the supreme field of merit for the world.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an8.57:1.12"
msgid "Sattamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

